Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1} and discard. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Heat a #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @?oil{1%drizzle} and some @?butter{1%knob} (if you have any). Once hot, add the leek and cook until soft, ~{6-7%minutes}, stirring regularly.

Add the @spring greens{112.5%g}(sliced) along with the @water for the greens{}, cover with a #tight-fitting lid{} and cook until wilted, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @British chicken breast{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a saucepan until it's 1-2cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the greens are cooking, heat a drizzle of @?oil{1%drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the chicken breasts to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned, ~{7-8%minutes} on each side.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the @honey{15%g} and @wholegrain mustard{17%g} to the pan and turn to coat the chicken in it until sticky, ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once glazed, transfer the chicken to a #chopping board{}, cover with #foil{} and leave to rest for ~{2%minutes}. Set the pan aside.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Return the (now empty) #frying pan{} to medium heat. Add the @apple and sage jelly{25%g} with a splash of @water{1%splash}, bring to a simmer, then remove from the heat.

Reheat the mash and vegetables if needed, then slice the chicken widthways into 5 or 6 pieces and serve on your plates with the mash and greens alongside.

Drizzle over the apple and sage sauce to finish.

Enjoy!